body:
# Capturing Errors & Enriching Events

Sentry automatically captures unhandled exceptions and promise rejections. For caught errors, network failures, and business logic violations, use the manual capture API.

## captureException

Capture caught errors with full stack traces:

```javascript
import * as Sentry from "@sentry/browser";

try {
  await processPayment(order);
} catch (err) {
  Sentry.captureException(err);
  showErrorToast("Payment failed");
}
```

Attach extra context inline:

```javascript
Sentry.captureException(err, {
  tags: { payment_provider: "stripe", order_id: order.id },
  extra: { amount: order.total, currency: order.currency },
  level: "fatal",
});
```

## captureMessage

Capture textual events when there is no exception object:

```javascript
Sentry.captureMessage("User exceeded rate limit", "warning");

// With context
Sentry.captureMessage("Config migration completed", {
  level: "info",
  tags: { migration: "v2-to-v3" },
});
```

Severity levels: `fatal`, `error`, `warning`, `log`, `info`, `debug`.

## Breadcrumbs

Breadcrumbs are a trail of events leading up to an error. The SDK auto-records DOM clicks, XHR/fetch requests, console logs, and navigation. Add custom breadcrumbs:

```javascript
Sentry.addBreadcrumb({
  category: "auth",
  message: `User ${user.email} logged in`,
  level: "info",
  data: { method: "oauth", provider: "google" },
});

Sentry.addBreadcrumb({
  category: "cart",
  message: "Item added to cart",
  level: "info",
  data: { sku: "WIDGET-42", quantity: 2, price: 29.99 },
});
```

## User Identification

Identify the current user so errors are grouped by user:

```javascript
// After login
Sentry.setUser({
  id: user.id,
  email: user.email,
  username: user.username,
  ip_address: "{{auto}}",
});

// On logout — clear the user
Sentry.setUser(null);
```

## Tags

Tags are indexed key-value pairs you can search and filter on in the Sentry UI:

```javascript
Sentry.setTag("feature_flag", "new-checkout-v2");
Sentry.setTag("tenant", customer.tenantId);
Sentry.setTag("subscription_tier", "enterprise");
```

## Context

Structured context is not indexed but appears in the event detail view:

```javascript
Sentry.setContext("order", {
  id: order.id,
  total: order.total,
  items: order.items.length,
  coupon: order.couponCode || "none",
});

Sentry.setContext("device", {
  battery: navigator.getBattery ? await navigator.getBattery().then(b => b.level) : "unknown",
  memory: navigator.deviceMemory || "unknown",
  cores: navigator.hardwareConcurrency || "unknown",
});
```

## Scoped Capture with withScope

Use `withScope` to attach context to a single event without polluting the global scope:

```javascript
Sentry.withScope((scope) => {
  scope.setTag("transaction", "checkout");
  scope.setLevel("warning");
  scope.setUser({ id: user.id, email: user.email });
  scope.setContext("cart", { items: cart.items, total: cart.total });
  Sentry.captureException(new Error("Checkout validation failed"));
});
// Global scope is unaffected after this block
```

## Global, Isolation, and Current Scopes

Sentry has three scope layers:

```javascript
// Global scope — applies to ALL events
Sentry.getGlobalScope().setTag("app_version", "2.1.0");

// Isolation scope — per-request in servers (setUser, setTag write here)
Sentry.getIsolationScope().setUser({ id: request.userId });

// Current scope — local to withScope callbacks
Sentry.getCurrentScope().setExtra("debug_data", payload);
```

## Extras

Attach arbitrary key-value data (not indexed, appears in event details):

```javascript
Sentry.setExtra("response_body", JSON.stringify(apiResponse));
Sentry.setExtra("retry_count", retryCount);
```
